column5: Title says it all, 4 of us went out for very first time, set up in anchor bay, and had first fish at dawn. Went 7 for 9 on the morning. We couldn't believe it, most caught on Mepps musky killers in 8-9 feet of water. Hope you enjoy, will be going back. Doug
Wow, excellent day on the water!
It was Pezman, way beyond our expectations.
Nice fish! Keep meaning to head down there since I don't live that far away from it.
